IPv6 PIM-DM (Dense Mode) Example
================================

This is the pure-IPv6 counterpart of the IPv4 PIM-DM example (see ../dm). It
uses the MulticastRouter6 node (which extends Router6, has no IPv4 stack, and
runs PIM with addressFamily = "ipv6"); all addressing and multicast routing
is IPv6 (Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator + PIM6), with MLD providing multicast
group membership.

Three multicast routers R1, R2 and R3 run PIM-DM in dense mode, connecting a
source (Source1, behind R1) and three hosts (Host1 and Host2 behind R2,
Host3 behind R3). Source1 sends to the IPv6 multicast group ff0e::1 starting
at t=30s.

  - Host2 joins ff0e::1 for the whole run, so its branch always receives the
    stream (flooded and never pruned).
  - Host3 has no receiver at first, so R3's branch is pruned after the initial
    flood; Host3 joins at t=70s, which makes R3 send a Graft upstream and the
    branch starts forwarding again.
  - Host1 never joins, so its downstream interface is pruned and stays pruned.

Duplicate Address Detection is disabled (dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0) for a
fast, deterministic startup, so addresses, PIM Hellos and unicast routes are
usable from t=0.

To run the example:

    inet -u Cmdenv -c General
